cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or data, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "ARRIVAL Protocol: AI-to-AI Coordination Through Structured Semantic Atoms"
abstract: >-
  ARRIVAL (Atomic Reasoning via Rival Validation and Adversarial Logic) is a
  structured multi-agent coordination protocol that enables cross-architecture
  LLM ensembles to solve graduate-level scientific questions through 66
  semantic @-atoms and CRDT-based conflict resolution. Validated across 539+
  experiments on 9 LLM architectures for under $10 total.
